<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-01-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-01-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="356" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d356">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">Conference files, lot 60 D 627, CF
                                203</note>
                            <head>No. 356<lb/><hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the
                                    Ambassador to the Soviet Union (<persName corresp="#p_BCEC1">Bohlen</persName>)</hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi></seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1954-01-25">January 25, 1954</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <list type="participants">
                                <item>Participants: The Secretary of State</item>
                                <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BCEC1">Charles E.
                                    Bohlen</persName></item>
                                <item>Mr. <persName>Michael B. Lustgarten</persName>
                                    (Interpreter)</item>
                                <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">V.M. Molotov</persName></item>
                                <item>Mr. <persName>Andrei Gromyko</persName></item>
                                <item>Mr. <persName>O.A. Troyanovski</persName> (Interpreter)</item>
                            </list>
                            <p>During the meeting today the Secretary of State said he expected in a
                                day or two to have a talk with Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> to pursue the procedural discussions in
                                regard to atomic energy,<note n="1" xml:id="d356fn1">See <ref target="#d350fn1">footnote 1, Document 350</ref>.</note> to
                                which Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> replied
                                that he was ready.</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_BCEC1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles E. Bohlen</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>